TITLE:: JPverb
summary:: Algorithmic reverberator, designed to produce long and rich reverberant tails.
categories:: UGens>Reverbs
RELATED:: Overviews/DEIND, Classes/Greyhole, Classes/JPverbRaw

DESCRIPTION::
image::JPverb-logo-small.png::
An algorithmic reverb, inspired by the lush chorused sound of certain vintage Lexicon and Alesis reverberation units. Designed to sound great with synthetic sound sources, rather than sound like a realistic space.

Developed as part of the LINK::Overviews/DEIND:: project.

NOTE::Please increase server realtime memory for this to work properly::
code::
s.options.memSize_(65536 * 4);
s.reboot;
::


CLASSMETHODS::
private:: categories

METHOD:: ar

note::This UGen always generates a stereo signal.::

argument::in
input to the reverb. Either an array of two audio signals (stereo), or a mono audiosignal.

argument::t60
approximate reverberation time in seconds code::(0.1..60 sec):: (code::T60:: - the time for the reverb to decay by 60db when code::damp == 0:: ). Does not effect early reflections.

argument::damp
controls damping of high-frequencies as the reverb decays. 0 is no damping, 1 is very strong damping. Values should be between code::(0..1)::.

argument::size
scales size of delay-lines within the reverberator, producing the impression of a larger or smaller space. Values below 1 can sound metallic. Values should be between code::(0.5..5)::.

argument::earlyDiff
controls shape of early reflections. Values of 0.707 or more produce smooth exponential decay. Lower values produce a slower build-up of echoes. Values should be between code::(0..1)::.

argument::modDepth
depth code::(0..1):: of delay-line modulation. Use in combination with modFreq to set amount of chorusing within the structure.

argument::modFreq
frequency code::(0..10 Hz):: of delay-line modulation. Use in combination with modDepth to set amount of chorusing within the structure.

argument::low
multiplier code::(0..1):: for the reverberation time within the low band.

argument::mid
multiplier code::(0..1):: for the reverberation time within the mid band.

argument::high
multiplier code::(0..1):: for the reverberation time within the high band.

argument::lowcut
frequency code::(100..6000 Hz):: at which the crossover between the low and mid bands of the reverb occurs.

argument::highcut
frequency code::(1000..10000 Hz):: at which the crossover between the mid and high bands of the reverb occurs.

returns::
a UGen.

EXAMPLES::

Minimal example (headphones recommended):

code::
s.options.memSize_(65536 * 4);
s.reboot;

{
	var src = SoundIn.ar(0)!2; // stereo input
	var rev = JPverb.ar(
		src,
		\t60.kr(1,           0.05),
		\damp.kr(0,          0.05),
		\size.kr(1,          0.05),
		\earlydiff.kr(0.707, 0.05),
		\mdepth.kr(5,        0.05),
		\mfreq.kr(2,         0.05),
		\lowx.kr(1,          0.05),
		\midx.kr(1,          0.05),
		\highx.kr(1,         0.05),
		\lowband.kr(500,     0.05),
		\highband.kr(2000,   0.05)
	);

	Mix([src, rev]) * 0.1;
}.play
::

